com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.plugin

Class AssemblerInput.Read

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.plugin.AssemblerInput.Read
  • Enclosing class:
    AssemblerInput

    public static class AssemblerInput.Read
extends Object
    Represents a single read or input contig. A read may either be 1 unpaired sequence, or 2 paired sequences. These are supplied to the assembly algorithm via getReads().getNextReadPair()

    Since different sequencing technologies orientate paired data in different relative orientations, paired data can be obtained in 2 different ways:

    1. Normalized such that the 2nd read is expected to appear in the same orientation as the first, but to the right. In other words, Forward/Forward orientation (e.g. SOLiD data style)
      The reads and expected distance in this case should be obtained using getReadNormalized(), getMateNormalized() and getExpectedMateDistanceNormalized()
      Alternatively use getReadNormalized() and getMateNormalizedReversed() to get the reads as forward/reverse (e.g. Illumina data style)
    2. Unnormalized using getRead(), getMate(), getExpectedMateDistanceForRead(), getExpectedMateDistanceForMate(). For a full discussion of what data means in this case, see PairedReads
    It is recommended that most implementations use the normalized system. See PairedReads for a full discussion of what unnormalized expected distances mean.

    If the assembly algorithm specified that it supports input contigs (see Assembler.supportsInputContigs() then instead of a read representing a sequence or paired of sequences, it may be a contig, in which case it will return null from getRead() and instead return a non-null value from getContig().

      • getContig

        public SequenceAlignmentDocument getContig()
        If this read represents a contig as input to the assembler, returns that contig. If this read is a sequence or pair of sequences, this method will return null in which case getRead() will return a non-null value. getContig will only return non-null values if Assembler.supportsInputContigs() returned true.
        Returns:
        the input contig or null if this read is a sequence or pair of sequences.

      • getIndexOfAssemblyReferenceSequenceForContig

        public int getIndexOfAssemblyReferenceSequenceForContig()
        If this read represents a contig (i.e. if getContig() returned non-null) which has a reference sequence (i.e. getContig().getContigReferenceSequenceIndex() returns a non-negative value) and that reference sequence is being treated as a reference sequence for this assembly, then this method returns the index of the reference sequence in the assembly input. (that could be retrieved using AssemblerInput.getReferenceSequence(int, jebl.util.ProgressListener) or -1 if this contig does not contain a reference sequence that is being treated as an input reference sequence to the assembler.
        Returns:
        the index of the reference sequence or -1.

      • getRead

        public NucleotideSequenceDocument getRead()
        Gets the first read in the pair or the single read if the read is unpaired. See AssemblerInput.Read for a discussion of the various get methods.
        Returns:
        the first read in the pair or the single read if the read is unpaired. This will never return null if the Assembler.supportsInputContigs() return false. If Assembler.supportsInputContigs() returns true then getRead() may return null in which case getContig() will return a non-null value

        public int getExpectedMateDistanceNormalized()

        Returns:

      • getReadNormalized

        public NucleotideSequenceDocument getReadNormalized()
        Gets the first read in the pair or the single read if the read is unpaired. This is expected to be used in conjunction with getExpectedMateDistanceNormalized() and either getMateNormalized() or getMateNormalizedReversed(). See AssemblerInput.Read for a discussion of the various get methods.
        Returns:
        the read normalized in direction so that its mate pair will appear to the right of it and with the same orientation

      • getMateNormalized

        public NucleotideSequenceDocument getMateNormalized()
        Gets the second read in the pair or null if the read is unpaired. This is expected to be used in conjunction with getReadNormalized() and getExpectedMateDistanceNormalized() See AssemblerInput.Read for a discussion of the various get methods.
        Returns:
        the mate normalized in direction so that its mate pair will appear to the left of it and with the same orientation. Will return null if the read is unpaired.

      • getMateNormalizedReversed

        public NucleotideSequenceDocument getMateNormalizedReversed()
        Gets the second read in the pair or null if the read is unpaired normalized such that the 2 reads are forward-reverse orientated. This is expected to be used in conjunction with getReadNormalized() and getExpectedMateDistanceNormalized() where getReadNormalized() returns the forward read, getMateNormalizedReversed() returns the reverse read and getExpectedMateDistanceNormalized() returns the distance between them. See AssemblerInput.Read for a discussion of the various get methods.
        Returns:
        the mate normalized in direction so that its mate pair will appear to the left of it and with the opposite orientation. Will return null if the read is unpaired.
